a is popular for its natural beauty places, including its varied bio-diversity, high rainfall, dense rainforest, and many other sites, and all of these places together make Meghalaya one of the most popular tourist destinations in India. If one wants to spend their vacation peacefully, away from the city's hectic life, and around nature, then Meghalaya is a perfect choice for them. Lack of connectivity can be an issue here for the visitors, but living under nature's touch with its own way of surviving and living, one will truly feel blessed to have visited this state. The Northeastern part of Meghalaya is bounded by the borders of Assam, whereas the Southwestern part of the state is surrounded by Bangladesh's boundary, and that's why one can find not only Indian but also Bangladeshi tourists on their trip to Meghalaya. The tribal community of Meghalaya, which includes Jaintias, Garos, and Khasis, is one of the most popular tribal communities of India, and the tribal communities which are listed above, contribute to the major population of the state. There are many tourist spots that can amaze and refresh the mind of the visitors, and this state will also surprise the tourists with a myriad of tourist attractions that one would surely include in their list. Tourists come here to take a break from their busy and hectic city work life and escape to forests and lush green valleys which cover the state from all directions. A pine-fresh mountain state among the Seven Sisters of India, Meghalaya has many things to offer to the visitors along with its gorgeous places covered with natural beauty, and visitors would never mind staying in this at least for a week. Meghalaya will surely refresh one's mind and make their heart happy with its pleasant weather and handicrafts made by its native tribal community. This article talks about all such tourist places of Meghalaya that one cannot afford to miss while having a visit to this beautiful state of clouds. 1. Mawphlang Sacred Fo